{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"449a045d-9ee0-4a9c-8dbd-a02f3c286315","content":"To switch to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC), you need to make these changes:\n\n**1. Configure your NuGet.org package** — In NuGet.org package settings, add a trusted publisher linking your GitHub repo, branch, and workflow file.\n\n**2. Update your workflow:**\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write   # Required for OIDC token\n      contents: read\n\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      # Build/pack steps...\n\n      - name: Push to NuGet\n        run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg\n          --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**Key differences:**\n- Add `permissions: id-token: write` to the job\n- Remove `--api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}` from `dotnet nuget push`\n- No secret needed — the OIDC token is automatically exchanged with NuGet.org\n- Delete the `NUGET_API_KEY` repository secret once confirmed working\n\n**3. NuGet.org setup** — Go to your package → Manage → Publishing → \"Add Trusted Publisher\" and fill in your GitHub org/repo, workflow filename, and optionally the environment/branch.\n\nThis eliminates long-lived secrets and scopes publishing to specific workflows/branches.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cacc7444-a16a-4f60-8249-61027f4ef9fd","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about switching from using a NuGet API key secret to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC) in their GitHub Actions publish workflow. This is a general knowledge question about GitHub Actions and NuGet trusted publishing - I don't need to look at any specific files since there's no repository here.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about what changes are needed to switch to NuGet trusted publishing with OIDC.","outputTokens":447,"requestId":"A409:156E46:13BCC1B:162C80E:69F93F43"},"id":"42869717-2bfa-449f-a95f-ace590238192","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:52:30.024Z","parentId":"b0229e6a-cd0d-455f-a90c-14988bb6389c"}
